    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi, Molly,</p>
<p>Fall came quickly this year, didn&#39;t it?  I love autumn, and after our (not your) hot summer, I thought I would be happier than ever when it arrived.  But it showed up so early, I was shocked.  Last weekend in upstate New York 50 per cent of the trees were already bare, and normally we hit peak this coming weekend.</p>
<p>I LOVE the book Pure Dessert.  I make the Almond Cake all the time, and I will try this one right away. </p>
<p>Do you think it would be good made with apricots when they are available?  I usually can&#39;t get any good local apricots here.  Even when they are available at the farmer&#39;s market, I generally find them to be mealy and unpleasant to eat out of hand.  But cooked &#8211; poached, in a cake, in a tart &#8211; they can be delicious.  I just got some lovely Austrian apricot brandy, similar to a grappa, so I am thinking ahead to the next apricot season when small glasses of it would be lovely after dinner.   What do you think?</p>
    </div>

